        "text": "<@UC21F8Q48> I love the <https:\/\/futureofcoding.slack.com\/archives\/C5T9GPWFL\/p1728520021525509|power graphic>. Feels like the *problem of the era*! What *power* means to me is human em*power*ment – more autonomy for the individual to choose the life they want to live. So, that translates to how *useful* is any tool to enable a human to do *decide* how they want to live. But it's really *difficult to measure absolutely* because it's relative to each individual – we all have different desires. For me that starts at the *interface* because that's currently where human freedom is immediately lost – as in, I can't alter the interface of apps I use. What comes to mind is giving end-users a way to extend the ease of Excel with a WYSIWYG UI (like Wix :wink:). But no-code power tools are mostly (if not all) SaaS and require a leap in understanding for the (power) user. Hmm... a great nut to try and crack.",
